## Security Insight 1: Unswitched Ethernet
On unswitched Ethernet (hub), every packet is received by every host. NIC decides if its for that host.
You can configure card to forward all packets (promiscuous mode).
Threat: Password sniffing.
My fix: WRT300N is switched, not hub. Mitigation: WPA2 + dont share WiFi.

